column7: A mixture of finely and coarsely ground animal bones and slaughter-house waste products.

column7: A mixture of several organic and mineral materials such as bran wheat, castor bean, straw, lime, rock phosphate, ashes etc., inoculated with microorganisms and fermented. The so-called "bokashi process" is typically applied to food and farmyard waste and its composition and properties can vary greatly.
A viscous substance resulting from refining sugarcane or sugar beets into sugar.
A viscous, dark and sucrose-rich syrup produced during the sugar extraction and refining process and used as organic fertiliser.
A humus-like material resulting from the digestion and aerobic decomposition of organic materials (typically waste), carried out by various species of worms.
Insects' excreta, used as an organic fertiliser.
A liquid by-product of human metabolism, which can be used as organic fertiliser.

column7: The by-product of the extraction of oil from rapeseeds. This term can be used to describe the meal obtained from both the spontaneous varieties (unsuitable for human and animal consumption due to the high erucic acid and glucosinolates content) and the low erucic acid, low glucosinolates cultivars known as canola. To further specify the variery, use the variety field.
